{
  "stem": "4361.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, the--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My maiden name is Fischman.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First name was Golda, but my nickname and a name I was-- still am mostly known by is Baba.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was born on September 7, 1925 in a town called Sighet, or Sziget.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At the time, it was Romania, and this town is in northern Transylvania.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Romanian spelling is S-I-G-H-E-T.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And eventually, later on when the Hungarians occupied that part of Romania, it became Sziget.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "With a different spelling, S-Z-I-G-E-T.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I said, I was born after the First World War in 1925.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Prior to that, Sighet and Transylvania was part of the Austro-Hungarian empire, and the reason I mention this is that I was bilingual.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My parents were a part of the Austrian-- Austro-Hungarian regime and life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the language spoken at home was Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My memories of my childhood are the best of my life because I had a very loving, caring, wonderful father and mother, two brothers, and a sister who pampered me very much.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was the youngest of the four children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had aunts and uncles, and it was a very warm, supportive, protective family and a well-to-do family.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we had a very full, rich life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "From early on, there were two things guiding my life, and that was to get an education, to learn, learning, to be Jewish, and in those days, to be a nice, in quotes, girl, which meant to be very soft, modest, as my mother used to say, and just be nice.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so this is how I grew up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't think I was always very submissive, but by and large, I went along, and it was an easy life, a good life.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was the youngest of four children.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
